IV. Completed Experiment Registry
Experiment 1: Recall & Dependency Stability
•	Observed: Label-dependent ground collapsed (0.66 failure) under shuffle.
•	Conclusion: Structural dependency (e.g., v_tl_has_parent) yielded 1.0 recall. Persistence is driven by Delta Invariants.
Experiment 3: Geodesic Construction
•	Process: Anchor nodes (KLIA/IGARI) $\rightarrow$ Forward Solve $\rightarrow$ Inverse Closure.
•	Result: Closure residuals maintained within absolute max of $6.2 \times 10^{-5}$ meters.
Experiment 4 & 5: Branching & Aliasing
•	Branching: N/S variants preserved without forced collapse.
•	Aliasing: Meter-based tolerance ($\epsilon_m$) successfully prevented "phantom nodes" from rounding drift.
 
V. Context Layer: Moon/Light Forks
The pipeline implements a bounded-null lunar gate.
•	Logic: If Moon Elevation $< 0 \rightarrow$ Moon Lux $= 0$.
•	Outcome: Direct lunar terms are strictly gated. Any residual skyglow is shunted to a separate background witness channel.
•	Forks: V2 supports 4-way multiplicity (fork mirroring) for systematic model replication.
 
